(325, 1, 'Départements : la droite à l''assaut des présidences', '["http:\\/\\/i.f1g.fr\\/media\\/figaro\\/805x453_crop\\/2015\\/04\\/01\\/XVM81b044fc-d88c-11e4-b167-6ada4245ef4d.jpg"]', '["Le Front national pr\\u00e9sentera jeudi des candidats \\u00e0 la pr\\u00e9sidence des 14 d\\u00e9partements o\\u00f9 il a des \\u00e9lus. Ils n''ont aucune chance de l''emporter, malgr\\u00e9 la forte progression r\\u00e9alis\\u00e9e par leur parti, mais pour Marine Le Pen, l''enjeu de ce troisi\\u00e8me tour est ailleurs: faute d''avoir r\\u00e9ussi \\u00e0 convaincre des \\u00e9lus UMP de la rejoindre, elle veut une nouvelle fois d\\u00e9montrer la \\u00abproximit\\u00e9 id\\u00e9ologique entre l''UMP et le PS\\u00bb.","Le FN a \\u00e9labor\\u00e9 une \\u00abcharte\\u00bb \\u00e0 l''intention des candidats \\u00e0 la pr\\u00e9sidence d''un d\\u00e9partement qui solliciterait son soutien. Ils doivent notamment s''engager \\u00e0 ne pas augmenter la fiscalit\\u00e9, \\u00e0 maintenir les services publics de proximit\\u00e9, \\u00e0 lutter contre les gaspillages et les fraudes sociales, \\u00e0 refuser toute subvention \\u00e0 des projets communautaristes et, enfin, \\u00e0 organiser des r\\u00e9f\\u00e9rendums locaux.","L''accord n''a pas trouv\\u00e9 preneur, y compris dans les trois d\\u00e9partements o\\u00f9 les bin\\u00f4mes lep\\u00e9nistes ont fait leurs meilleurs scores: l''Aisne, le Vaucluse et le Gard. Dans le Gard, \\u00abla droite pr\\u00e9f\\u00e8re laisser le d\\u00e9partement aux socialistes plut\\u00f4t que d''\\u00eatre \\u00e9lue avec les voix du Front, alors que le FN ne r\\u00e9clame aucune vice-pr\\u00e9sidence!\\u00bb, accuse Marine Le Pen, alors que l''UMP et l''UDI ont trouv\\u00e9 une autre solution (lire ci-dessous). La pr\\u00e9sidente du FN s''insurge d''autant plus qu''elle ne voit \\u00abrien\\u00bb, dans les huit conditions pos\\u00e9es par la charte frontiste, que les candidats de l''UMP ne pourraient \\u00abassumer\\u00bb, \\u00e9tant donn\\u00e9 \\u00ableurs propres engagements\\u00bb. \\u00abC''est la preuve ultime et spectaculaire que le ni-ni est, en r\\u00e9alit\\u00e9, une vaste escroquerie\\u00bb, assure-t-elle, en pointant les \\u00abd\\u00e9sistements r\\u00e9ciproques\\u00bb du second tour.","\\u00ab&#8202;La droite pr\\u00e9f\\u00e8re laisser le d\\u00e9partement aux socialistes plut\\u00f4t que d''\\u00eatre \\u00e9lue avec les voix du Front, alors que le FN ne r\\u00e9clame aucune vice-pr\\u00e9sidence&#8202;!&#8202;\\u00bb","Dans ces d\\u00e9partements, et m\\u00eame ailleurs, des bin\\u00f4mes de droite se sont effectivement retir\\u00e9s en appelant \\u00e0 \\u00abfaire barrage au Front national\\u00bb, mais ces cas sont ultraminoritaires. Au troisi\\u00e8me tour, tout danger de faire \\u00e9lire un pr\\u00e9sident FN \\u00e9tant \\u00e9cart\\u00e9, le bureau de l''UMP qui s''est r\\u00e9uni lundi s''est born\\u00e9 \\u00e0 rappeler qu''\\u00abil appartiendra \\u00e0 chaque majorit\\u00e9 d\\u00e9partementale de la droite r\\u00e9publicaine et du centre d''\\u00e9lire son pr\\u00e9sident, dans le respect des engagements pris devant les \\u00e9lecteurs\\u00bb.","Avant ce bureau politique, Nicolas Sarkozy et Jean-Christophe Lagarde s''\\u00e9taient vus pour r\\u00e9gler les quelques probl\\u00e8mes de choix de candidat qui pouvaient se poser entre l''UMP et l''UDI. Les patrons de la droite et du centre ont rejet\\u00e9 d''une m\\u00eame voix toute perspective d''\\u00abaccord de gestion\\u00bb avec la gauche dans les d\\u00e9partements o\\u00f9 l''UMP-UDI n''a obtenu qu''une majorit\\u00e9 relative, mais ils sont conscients que le FN pourrait en profiter pour tenter de revenir dans le jeu \\u00e0 la faveur, par exemple, des votes budg\\u00e9taires.","\\u00abLe syst\\u00e8me des bin\\u00f4mes renforce encore le risque de blocages\\u00bb, souligne Jean-Christophe Lagarde, puisque chaque assembl\\u00e9e d\\u00e9partementale est compos\\u00e9e d''un nombre pair de conseillers hommes et femmes. Le pr\\u00e9sident de l''UDI demande au gouvernement, auteur du nouveau mode de scrutin, \\u00abde prendre ses responsabilit\\u00e9s en proposant une loi qui stabilise les majorit\\u00e9s r\\u00e9gionales\\u00bb. Selon le pr\\u00e9sident de l''UDI, il suffirait \\u00abd''\\u00e9tendre aux d\\u00e9partements le 49-3 r\\u00e9gional\\u00bb. Dans les conseils r\\u00e9gionaux, le budget est adopt\\u00e9 sauf si l''opposition constitue une majorit\\u00e9 de substitution, avec un candidat \\u00e0 la pr\\u00e9sidence, susceptible d''adopter un contre-budget. Xavier Bertrand, qui pr\\u00e9voit des difficult\\u00e9s dans la gestion de l''Aisne, se dit \\u00e9galement \\u00abfavorable \\u00e0 un 49-3 d\\u00e9partemental\\u00bb."]', 'http://www.lefigaro.fr/politique/2015/04/01/01002-20150401ARTFIG00404-departements-la-droite-a-l-assaut-des-presidences.php', '', 'n', '2015-04-03 05:04:02'),
(326, 111, 'Muhammadu Buhari was the least bad presidential candidate in Nigeria. May he rise to his task', '["http:\\/\\/cdn.static-economist.com\\/sites\\/default\\/files\\/imagecache\\/full-width\\/images\\/print-edition\\/20150404_LDP006_1.jpg","http:\\/\\/cdn.static-economist.com\\/sites\\/default\\/files\\/imagecache\\/290-width\\/images\\/2015\\/02\\/articles\\/body\\/20150207_mam909_290.png"]', '["    ","FOR the first time, Nigerians have ejected an incumbent president at the ballot box, in a broadly peaceful election. Muhammadu Buhari, the former military dictator who has defeated Goodluck Jonathan, will now preside over Africa\\u2019s most populous country, biggest economy and weightiest global actor. This is joyful news for Nigeria\\u2014and Africa (see article).","One big reason to cheer is that Mr Jonathan has been such a dismal failure. So has his People\\u2019s Democratic Party (PDP), which has run Nigeria ever since the generals gave way to an elected civilian government in 1999. His administration has woefully failed to defeat an insurgency by Boko Haram, an Islamist extremist group that has tormented Nigeria\\u2019s north-east over the past few years. Mr Jonathan tried to improve farming and provide electricity to all, but proved unable to rebuild much of Nigeria\\u2019s hideously decrepit infrastructure. Above all, he was unwilling to tackle corruption, the country\\u2019s greatest scourge and the cause of much of its chaos. When the central bank\\u2019s respected governor complained that $20 billion had been stolen, Mr Jonathan sacked him. Nigeria is the biggest producer of oil on the continent, but most of its 170m-plus people still live on less than $2 a day. That is an indictment of successive governments.","","Thanks to the resilience and vitality of ordinary Nigerians, the economy has been growing fast, especially around Lagos, the thriving commercial hub. But that is largely despite the government, not because of it. And with the oil price sharply down, Nigerians could well become even poorer.","Nobody can be sure that the 72-year-old Mr Buhari will turn things around fast, if at all. His brief stint as the country\\u2019s leader 32 years ago, when he was a general, was little better than Mr Jonathan\\u2019s. His human-rights record was appalling. He detained thousands of opponents, silenced the press, banned political meetings and had people executed for crimes that were not capital offences when they were committed. He expelled 700,000 immigrants under the illusion that this would create jobs for Nigerians. His economic policies, which included the fixing of prices and bans on \\u201cunnecessary\\u201d imports, were both crass and ineffective.","  Nigeria in graphics: the issues behind the 2015 election    ","Yet there is reason to hope that he has learnt from past mistakes. Although not always with a good grace, Mr Buhari accepted defeat in three previous presidential elections. As a northerner, a Muslim and a former soldier, he has a better chance of restoring the morale of Nigeria\\u2019s miserable army, which is essential if it is to defeat Boko Haram. His All Progressives Congress is a ramshackle coalition of parties, but the calibre of a number of its leading lights is superior to that of the greedy and incompetent bigwigs who dominate the PDP. Above all, Mr Buhari, whose style is strikingly ascetic, has a reputation for honesty. Corruption in Nigeria is so ingrained that nobody should expect him to root it out overnight. But it is vital that the new president makes a start. His vice-presidential running mate is a pastor who has fought hard for human rights and cleaner government.","Setting an example","Since 1991, when an incumbent leader on the African continent\\u2014in little Benin\\u2014was for the first time peacefully ejected at the ballot box after three decades without genuine democracy, at least 30 governments and presidents have been voted out of office. Though that is an incomparably better record than in the Arab world, Africa has recently become patchier again. Mr Jonathan\\u2019s magnanimous concession of victory to Mr Buhari will be a terrific boost to democrats across the continent. Just hope and pray that Mr Buhari does not let them down."]', 'http://www.economist.com/news/leaders/21647616-muhammadu-buhari-was-least-bad-presidential-candidate-nigeria-may-he-rise-his', '', 'n', '2015-04-03 05:04:02'),
(327, 111, ' Iraq and Syria are ''finishing schools'' for foreign extremists, says UN report ', '["http:\\/\\/i.guim.co.uk\\/media\\/w-300\\/h--\\/q-95\\/c43ecdd0612601d467af05d8c36a2f133ce86112\\/0_0_5801_3482\\/500.jpg"]', '["Iraq and Syria have become \\u201cinternational finishing schools\\u201d for extremists according to a UN report which says the number of foreign fighters joining terrorist groups has spiked to more than 25,000 from more than 100 countries.","The panel of experts monitoring UN sanctions against al-Qaida estimates the number of overseas terrorist fighters worldwide increased by 71% between mid-2014 and March 2015.","It said the scale of the problem had increased over the past three years and the flow of foreign fighters was \\u201chigher than it has ever been historically\\u201d.","The overall number of foreign terrorist fighters has \\u201crisen sharply from a few thousand \\u2026 a decade ago to more than 25,000 today,\\u201d the panel said in its report to the UN security council, which was obtained by Associated Press.","The report said just two countries had drawn more than 20,000 foreign fighters: Syria and Iraq. They went to fight primarily for the Islamic State group but also the al-Nusra Front.","Looking ahead, the panel said the thousands of foreign fighters who travelled to Syria and Iraq were living and working in \\u201ca veritable \\u2018international finishing school\\u2019 for extremists\\u201d, as was the case in Afghanistan in the 1990s.","A military defeat of the Islamic State group in Syria and Iraq could have the unintended consequence of scattering violent foreign terrorist fighters across the world, the panel said. And while governments are focusing on countering the threat from fighters returning home, the panel said it was possible that some may be traumatised by what they saw and need psychological help, and that others may be recruited by criminal networks.","In addition to Syria and Iraq, the report said Afghan security forces estimated in March that about 6,500 foreign fighters were active in the country. And it said hundreds of foreigners were fighting in Yemen, Libya and Pakistan, about 100 in Somalia, and others in the Sahel countries in northern Africa, and in the Philippines.","The number of countries the fighters come from has also risen dramatically from a small group in the 1990s to more than 100 today \\u2014 more than half the countries in the world \\u2014 including some that have never had previous links with groups associated with al-Qaida, the panel said.","It cited the \\u201chigh number\\u201d of foreign fighters from Tunisia, Morocco, France and Russia, the increase in fighters from the Maldives, Finland and Trinidad and Tobago, and the first fighters from some countries in sub-Saharan Africa which it did not name. The groups had also found recruits from Britain and Australia.","The panel said the fighters and their networks posed \\u201can immediate and long-term threat\\u201d and \\u201can urgent global security problem\\u201d that needed to be tackled on many fronts and had no easy solution.","With globalised travel, it said, the chance of a person from any country becoming a victim of a foreign terrorist attack was growing \\u201cparticularly with attacks targeting hotels, public spaces and venues\\u201d.","But the panel noted that a longstanding terrorist goal is \\u201cgenerating public panic\\u201d and stressed that the response needed to \\u201cbe measured, effective and proportionate\\u201d.","It said the most effective policy was to prevent the radicalisation, recruitment and travel of would-be fighters.","The panel noted that less than 10% of basic information to identify foreign fighters had been put in global systems and called for greater intelligence sharing. As a positive example, it noted that the \\u201cwatchlist\\u201d in Turkey \\u2014 a key transit point to Syria and Iraq \\u2014 now included 12,500 individuals."]', 'http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/apr/02/iraq-and-syria-are-finishing-schools-for-foreign-extremists-says-un-report', 'y', 'n', '2015-04-03 05:04:02'),
(328, 111, 'Feds Nabbed For Big Bitcoin Heist Involving Gox And Silk Road', '["https:\\/\\/tctechcrunch2011.files.wordpress.com\\/2014\\/04\\/bitcoin-eagle1.jpg?w=738","https:\\/\\/tctechcrunch2011.files.wordpress.com\\/2015\\/04\\/rwg5gi5.png?w=693&#038;h=862","https:\\/\\/tctechcrunch2011.files.wordpress.com\\/2015\\/04\\/fxxxma3.png?w=1024&#038;h=707"]', '["New information in the Silk Road case is sending ripples of schadenfreude through the cryptocurrency community as it reacts to a foiled effort by two US Federal Agents to skim thousands of Bitcoin out of Silk Road and Mt. Gox coffers.","According to a statement issued by the United States Department of Justice on Monday, two federal agents are charged with wire fraud, money laundering and falsifying government documents for stealing Bitcoin while working on the Silk Road investigation.","The agents were part of a Baltimore-based task force investigating the Silk Road marketplace. Their mission included the task of building a relationship with Ross Ulbricht (aka \\u2018Dread Pirate Roberts\\u2019 the accused owner of Silk Road who was found guilty last month). The two agents leveraged their status as federal agents to mislead, pressure, and personally profit from their activities during the investigation \\u2013 all of it which went unreported or unnoticed to the departments that employed them.","Information in the criminal complaint revealed that the Baltimore task force gained administrator access to Silk Road after arresting one of its employees. Secret Service Agent Shaun Bridges then logged into the Silk Road admin account that afternoon to personally conduct sizeable thefts from Silk Road accounts.","This theft was the cornerstone of the alleged \\u201ckill for hire\\u201d requests that were part of the case against Ulbricht\\u2019s. After the BTC went missing, Ulbricht had offered money to kill an employee who he believed stole from the Silk Road. Little did he know that it was Bridges, acting as the employee, who did the siphoning.","What\\u2019s interesting is that these Bitcoins were moved from Silk Road to Mt. Gox by Shaun Bridges where he could exchange them from BTC to USD, giving him time to set up a LLC and open a bank account so he could send the funds back to the United States.","During that same time \\u2013 the other federal agent charged, Carl Force, reached out to Mark Karpeles of Mt. Gox via Linkedin and asked if he would back Force on a sale of 250 bitcoins. Force said he was a federal agent but was looking for other employment.","","During this time, Bridges\\u2019 funded his bank account with nine wires from Mt. Gox totaling $820,000 in a three month period. After completing these bank transfers, Bridges signed the seizure warrant against Mt. Gox, confiscating $5 million USD shutting down the Bitcoin exchange in the process. The affadavit charged that Mt. Gox was acting as a money services business without a license, unlawfully allowing people to exchange bitcoins to fiat currency \\u2013 an activity which Shaun Bridges had conducted just days before.","A lovely email from Carl Force after the Mt. Gox seizure mockingly told Karpeles that he should have partnered with him \\u2013 an offer which was declined by Karpeles a couple days before the shutdown. It\\u2019s important to note that Carl Force, a DEA Special Agent for 15 years \\u2013 was doubly employed during this time as a \\u2018Compliance Officer\\u2019 for a Bitcoin exchange called coinMKT where he personally invested $110,000 USD worth of bitcoin.","In fact Carl Force used his DEA access to illegally run criminal history checks against users of the exchange and illegally froze one of its individual customer\\u2019s accounts containing $297,000 USD worth of digital currency and $37,000 USD in cash. The account in question belonged to a California resident who worked as a self-employed actor \\u2013 unfortunately, due to a glitch in CoinMKT\\u2019s system preventing withdrawals over $10,000 \\u2013 this account was flagged gaining the attention of Carl Force to take control of the funds even though he lacked a sufficient legal basis on which to do so.","Claiming that the seizure was part of a federal investigation (which was faked), Carl Force then had coinMKT move the bitcoins to his personal account at Bitstamp. Thankfully, Bitstamp became suspicious and froze the account after they noticed Carl Force trying to withdraw $80,000 USD into a personal bank account \\u2013 while using the TOR (private) browser because he didnt wan\\u2019t the \\u201cNSA looking over [his] shoulder.\\u201d","It was only after Bitstamp talked to Bridges that Carl Force\\u2019s accounts were unfrozen and he was able to move the stolen Bitcoins which were exchanged to USD and transferred to his personal bank account. Carl Force\\u2019s made several real estate purchases, transferred some cash to off-shore banking accounts, and paid off his mortgage.","","Shaun Bridges and Carl Force stole millions of dollars worth of bitcoin and digital currency. The federal agents used a number of bitcoin exchanges, payment processors, and bank accounts in an attempt to move their funds between accounts and identities. Unfortunately for them, they were unfamiliar with how Bitcoin is inherently traceable and transparent with transaction flows. Thankfully, we can thank IRS Special Agent Gambaryan Tigran for piecing this together. In the end, this strange sad saga is one more step on the road to cryptocurrency\\u2019s mass adoption and acts mostly as a cautionary tale for those who think they can fool the hackers at their own game.","Editor\\u2019s Note: Lisa Cheng is the chief executive of the Vanbex Group, a cryptocurrency consulting firm."]', 'http://techcrunch.com/2015/04/01/feds-nabbed-for-big-bitcoin-heist-involving-gox-and-silk-road/#tmhmdj:C3Dk', 'n', 'y', '2015-04-03 05:04:02'),
