(353, 95, 'Privateer Holdings Closes $75 Million In Funding To Create The P&amp;G Of Pot', '["https:\\/\\/tctechcrunch2011.files.wordpress.com\\/2015\\/02\\/5457588964_83e9aba231_o.jpg?w=738"]', '["It\\u2019s high time the cannabis industry got some serious attention from investors. So it\\u2019s a good thing that Privateer Holdings, a company focusing on producing, distributing, and educating consumers about legal marijuana, has closed on a $75 million round of funding it will use to create new brands of cannabis products.","Privateer is a holding company that was designed to create, incubate, and to acquire companies in the cannabis industry. Today it has three principal holdings:","That\\u2019s just the start, though. Privateer has big plans to expand and add new brands as time goes on. And it hopes that the brands it creates and incubates will not only appeal to customers, but will also help legitimize the cannabis industry.","\\u201cWe\\u2019re in this really interesting stage at the end of prohibition,\\u201d Privateer CEO and co-founder Brendan Kennedy told me. \\u201cOur focus is on creating brands that fuel change, that change perceptions of the product and user \\u2014 brands that inspire trust, and brands that create legitimacy.\\u201d","That\\u2019s a mission that Privateer has been working on since 2010, when Kennedy and two friends decided to quit their day jobs and to focus on funding products that would move the industry forward. But they soon realized that just purely making investments in the usual VC or private equity model wouldn\\u2019t make sense in a fragmented market with few standards.","Instead, they decided to build a portfolio of products users could identify with and build an affinity toward. In that way, they\\u2019re not so different from P&amp;G, General Mills, Nestle, Coca-Cola, PepsiCo., or any of the other big conglomerates of consumer-facing brands out there today. The only difference is that they\\u2019re building brands around a market that is not totally legal today. But that\\u2019s quickly changing.","\\u201cThis is the next logical step in the transformation of this industry, as it changes from a market that operates in the shadows to a fully transparent market that\\u2019s out in the open,\\u201d Kennedy said.","A lot of progress has happened in the five years since Privateer was founded. As Kennedy notes, in 2010 medical cannabis was legal in just 15 states, and only about 29 percent of the U.S. population lived in areas. But now medical cannabis is legal in 23 states plus Washington, D.C., and fully legal in another four states. Today more than 72 percent of the population lives in areas where some form of marijuana is legal.","The broader availability of legal marijuana today means not just a bigger market opportunity, but also the chance to be a front-runner in standardizing how people buy \\u2014 and really, how they think about \\u2014 marijuana, whether it\\u2019s for medical or recreational use.","\\u201cOur thesis was that this will be a mainstream consumer product used by mainstream Americans, and they will be looking for mainstream professional brands that don\\u2019t insult or offend them,\\u201d Kennedy said.","Indeed, the days of buying a nondescript baggie of weed from a local delivery guy on a bike are coming to an end. Today\\u2019s cannabis buyers are increasingly sophisticated, educated and discerning consumers who have more information than ever about the particular strains of marijuana available to them, as well as their effects.","The first company in Privateer\\u2019s portfolio, Leafly, was all about helping to educate users on available cannabis products. When Leafly acquired the business in 2012, Leafly had about 100,000 visits a month and no revenue. Last month it hosted over 5 million visits and is now profitable.","More important to Privateer than simply providing an online resource for potential customers, Leafly also produces a large amount of data that can be applied to the company\\u2019s other lines of business. From Leafly, it knows what kind of people are searching for cannabis and medical cannabis, when they are searching for it and where they are searching for it.","Leafly \\u201creally informs us of the most popular strains and the most popular retail locations around the world,\\u201d according to Kennedy. Today about 75 percent of those searches occur in the U.S., with the remainder happening internationally.","That information will help inform the types of products produced by its existing brands, Tilray and Marley Natural. And it will probably be used to help build other brands over time.","Kennedy said he could see Privateer creating brands aimed at high-end cannabis connoisseurs and those on the value side of the equation. He compared it to the beer market, where there\\u2019s a segment for Sam Adams drinkers, and one for Heineken drinkers. And sometimes those brands end up being owned by the same company.","For now, though, the $75 million investment seems to legitimize what has been seen as a poor investment opportunity for years. And it was all anchored by Founders Fund, which announced its participation in January. Since then, the company has had a much easier time closing its round.","While other investors have come on board, they didn\\u2019t want to be named in the announcement. It turns out that some VC firms, high net worth individuals, and family trusts still don\\u2019t wish to be associated with a drug that is still illegal on a federal level.","\\u201cI said in January that the announcement by Founders Fund would give other smart investors permission to look at this industry,\\u201d Kennedy said. \\u201cThat was unfathomable five years ago.\\u201d","According to him, those investors are betting that Privateer will be able to build four or five billion-dollar brands in the cannabis space. And based on how things are going, they just might be right."]', 'http://techcrunch.com/2015/04/06/they-should-have-announced-at-420/', '', 'n', '2015-04-07 16:43:11'),
(354, 95, 'North Korea Can Miniaturize a Nuclear Weapon, U.S. Says ', '["http:\\/\\/media.gotraffic.net\\/images\\/iqubq0oiUbFs\\/v5\\/488x-1.jpg"]', '[" North Korea has deployed its new road-mobile KN-08 intercontinental ballistic missile and is capable of mounting a miniaturized nuclear warhead on it, the U.S.\\u2019s top homeland security commander said.","\\u201cOur assessment is that they have the ability to put a nuclear weapon on a KN-08 and shoot it at the homeland,\\u201d Admiral William Gortney, the head of the U.S. Northern Command, told reporters Tuesday at the Pentagon. \\u201cWe have not seen them do that\\u201d and \\u201cwe haven\\u2019t seen them test the KN-08.\\u201d","He said \\u201cyes sir\\u201d when asked if the U.S. thinks North Korea has succeeded in the complicated task of miniaturizing a warhead for use on such a missile. North Korea has conducted three nuclear tests since 2006.","Gortney\\u2019s remarks are the strongest to date by a U.S. military official about the status of the KN-O8 missile and North Korea\\u2019s progress in making a nuclear weapon small enough to put on it, although they reflected the customary caution about what\\u2019s going on in the insular country.","Gortney said in congressional testimony last month that the KN-08\\u2019s mobility \\u201cwill complicate our ability to provide warning and defense against an attack.\\u201d On Tuesday, he said that if North Korea were to fire a missile at the U.S., \\u201cI am confident we can knock it down.\\u201d","The KN-08 may have a maximum range of 9,000 kilometers (5,592 miles), far enough to reach the West Coast, aerospace engineer John Schilling and security analyst Henry Kan wrote in a report on \\u201c38 North,\\u201d a blog monitoring North Korea.","Past statements by the U.S. and South Korea that the North has gained the ability to miniaturize a nuclear weapon have been \\u201cfollowed by oddly parsed statements suggesting that maybe they haven\\u2019t,\\u201d Jeffrey Lewis, a specialist on East Asia nonproliferation issues at the Middlebury Institute of International Studies at Monterey, California, wrote in February on 38 North.","Gortney\\u2019s comment comes as U.S. Secretary of Defense Ashton Carter plans to visit Seoul on Thursday for talks on ways to bolster deterrence against North Korea. His Asian trip includes a stop in Japan and coincides with annual U.S.-South Korean military exercises that North Korea calls a rehearsal for nuclear war. The allies call the drills defensive in nature.","North Korea claimed after its last nuclear test in 2013 that it had the ability to hit the mainland U.S. with nuclear-tipped missiles. It also defied United Nations Security Council resolutions by test-firing ballistic missiles.","North Korea probably needs to improve the reliability and accuracy of its intercontinental ballistic missile, \\u201churdles that even more advanced industrialized countries would find challenging,\\u201d Schilling and Kan wrote.","\\u201cNorth Korea is seriously pursuing the deployment of more capable, longer-range, more survivable weapons,\\u201d they wrote. \\u201cIn short, North Korea has already achieved a level of delivery system development that will allow it to establish itself as a small nuclear power in the coming years.\\u201d"]', 'http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-04-07/n-korea-can-mount-miniature-nuclear-weapon-u-s-admiral-says', '', 'n', '2015-04-08 04:37:47'),
(355, 2, 'Now You Can Embed Images And GIFs From Imgur', '["https:\\/\\/tctechcrunch2011.files.wordpress.com\\/2015\\/04\\/imgur-embed-screenshot.jpg?w=586"]', '["If you\\u2019re an online writer or publisher and you want to include a picture from Imgur, it\\u2019s now easy to do so in a totally legit way thanks to the image-sharing site\\u2019s new embedding capabilities.","In other words, the company says that when you\\u2019re looking at any public image  or GIF on Imgur, you\\u2019ll now find an embed option in the \\u201cPost Options\\u201d menu, allowing you to copy a line of HTML and reproduce the content\\u00a0on your site.","Not that it was all that hard before to download and re-upload an image. Nonetheless, adding embedding capabilities has helped sites like YouTube and Twitter distribute their content across the web, and we might see something\\u00a0similar here \\u2014 so even if you aren\\u2019t someone who embeds pictures yourself, you might start seeing a lot more Imgur content on other sites.","Plus, by supporting embeds, Imgur gets more control over the experience \\u2014 for one thing, it guarantees that the image will be reproduced with proper attribution. Embeds could also give Imgur (and the users who upload\\u00a0these images in the first place) more data about how the content\\u00a0is being published, shared and viewed.","One thing to keep in mind is that not all sites will immediately support this embed code. Sadly, TechCrunch\\u2019s version of WordPress is pretty restrictive, so I had to go with a screenshot above, instead of an embed. (Hopefully we can get that fixed soon.)"]', 'http://techcrunch.com/2015/04/07/embed-this-image/', '', 'n', '2015-04-08 05:21:46'),
(356, 2, 'Google Will Shut Down Moderator On July 31', '["https:\\/\\/tctechcrunch2011.files.wordpress.com\\/2015\\/03\\/6054732942_31205d8ac8_o.jpg?w=738","https:\\/\\/tctechcrunch2011.files.wordpress.com\\/2015\\/04\\/2015-04-07_1054.png?w=1024&#038;h=564"]', '["Google Moderator, a tool for crowdsourcing and ranking user-submitted questions for online and offline events, is shutting down on July 31.","The service, which launched in 2008, survived various \\u201cspring cleaning\\u201d rounds over the years. It\\u00a0was occasionally used by the White House\\u00a0and featured prominently during the 2012 presidential election. Now, however, Google has decided that it doesn\\u2019t have the usage it hoped for.","It looks\\u00a0like the development of\\u00a0Moderator stopped quite a while ago. The last copyright notice on the site is from 2011 and the service\\u00a0never got any of the design updates Google introduced over the last few years. For the most part,\\u00a0it still\\u00a0looks just like it did back in 2008.","","In many ways,\\u00a0it\\u2019s surprising Moderator lasted this long. After Google cut a number of former Google Labs projects in 2011 \\u2014 which is where Moderator got its start as a \\u201c20 percent project\\u201d \\u2014 it looked like Moderator would also get the axe. Somehow, though, the project\\u00a0survived.","The Moderator project was originally led\\u00a0by Katie Jacobs Stanton, who went on to become Barack Obama\\u2019s Director of Citizen Participation and is now the VP of Global Media at Twitter.","Moderator users \\u2014 and there shouldn\\u2019t be all that many given how dormant the project has been \\u2014 will be able to download their data from Google Takeout starting on March 30.\\u00a0This data will be available for at least two years. The last day to create new content on the service is June 30, and Moderator will shut down completely on July 31.","It\\u2019ll be interesting to see if this is a one-off announcement or if it\\u2019ll kick off another round of \\u201cspring cleaning\\u201d at Google."]', 'http://techcrunch.com/2015/04/07/dont-cry-for-google-moderator/#.nwqqnk:sTQ0', '', 'n', '2015-04-08 05:24:06'),
(357, 1, 'U.S. Dot-Com Bubble Was Nothing Compared to Today’s China Prices ', '["http:\\/\\/media.gotraffic.net\\/images\\/iebSgEQVJC_0\\/v1\\/488x-1.jpg"]', '[" The world-beating surge in Chinese technology stocks is making the heady days of the dot-com bubble look tame by comparison.","The industry is leading gains in China\\u2019s $6.9 trillion stock market, sending valuations to an average 220 times reported profits, the most expensive level among global peers. When the Nasdaq Composite Index peaked in March 2000, technology companies in the U.S. had a mean price-to-earnings ratio of 156.","Like the rise of the Internet two decades ago, China\\u2019s technology shares are being fueled by a compelling story: the ruling Communist Party is promoting the industry to wean Asia\\u2019s biggest economy from its reliance on heavy manufacturing and property development. In an echo of the late 1990s, Chinese stocks are also gaining support from lower interest rates, a boom in initial public offerings and an influx of money from novice investors.","The good news is the technology sector makes up a smaller portion of China\\u2019s equity market than it did in the U.S. 15 years ago, limiting the potential fallout from a selloff. The bad news is that any reversal in the industry will saddle individual investors with losses and risk putting an end to the Shanghai Composite Index\\u2019s rally to a seven-year high.","\\u201cChinese technology stocks do resemble the dot-com bubble,\\u201d Vincent Chan, the Hong Kong-based head of China research at Credit Suisse Group AG, Switzerland\\u2019s second-biggest bank, said in an interview on April 2. \\u201cGiven stocks fell 50 to 70 percent when that bubble burst in 2000, these small-cap Chinese shares may face big corrections when this one deflates.\\u201d","China\\u2019s government is boosting spending on science and technology as a faltering industrial sector drags down economic growth to the weakest pace in 25 years. In March, Premier Li Keqiang outlined an \\u201cInternet Plus\\u201d plan to link web companies with manufacturers. Authorities also plan to give foreign investors access to Shenzhen\\u2019s stock market, the hub for technology firms, through an exchange link with Hong Kong.","Among global technology companies with a market value of at least $1 billion, all 50 of the top performers this year are from China. The sector has the highest valuations among 10 industry groups on mainland exchanges after the CSI 300 Technology Index climbed 69 percent in 2015 through Tuesday, more than three times faster than the broader measure.","The CSI 300 technology gauge fell 2.1 percent at the 11:30 a.m. local-time break, the most among all industries and heading for its largest decline in almost two weeks. The broader index advanced 0.2 percent.","Technology companies have posted the biggest gains among Chinese IPOs during the past year, helped by a regulatory ceiling on valuations for new share sales. Beijing Tianli Mobile Service Integration Co. is the top performer among 147 offerings during the period after surging 1,871 percent from its offer price to trade at 379 times earnings.","Valuations in China are now higher than those in the U.S. at the height of the dot-com bubble just about any way you slice them. The average Chinese technology stock has a price-to-earnings ratio 41 percent above that of U.S. peers in 2000, while the median valuation is twice as expensive and the market capitalization-weighted average is 12 percent higher, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.","\\u201cIt\\u2019s a bubble in the making,\\u201d Teng Bingsheng, an associate dean at the Cheung Kong Graduate School of Business in Beijing, said in an interview on Tuesday. \\u201cValuations are extremely expensive.\\u201d","China lacks some of the most extreme excesses of the dot-com era because of regulations that require any company seeking a listing on the nation\\u2019s biggest exchanges to be profitable.","\\u201cHigh valuations don\\u2019t necessarily mean that they are unreasonable,\\u201d Gui Haoming, the Shanghai-based director of the wealth management research department at Shenwan Hongyuan Group Co., the nation\\u2019s second-biggest brokerage by market value, said on April 3. \\u201cSome of the valuations can be digested by high earnings growth.\\u201d","The smaller size of China\\u2019s technology sector also makes it less likely that a reversal in the rally will cause a broader tumble in equities. The industry accounts for 13 percent of the country\\u2019s overall market capitalization, compared with about 31 percent for the U.S. in 2000, data compiled by Bloomberg show. It took the Standard &amp; Poor\\u2019s 500 Index about seven years to recover from the aftermath of the dot-com bubble. The Nasdaq Composite has yet to reclaim its high.","While Haitong Securities Co.\\u2019s Chen Ruiming says it\\u2019s hard to predict when China\\u2019s rally will end, he sees growing signs of speculative behavior.","The use of margin debt to trade mainland shares has climbed to all-time highs, while investors are opening stock accounts at a record pace. More than two-thirds of new investors have never attended or graduated from high school, according to a survey by China\\u2019s Southwestern University of Finance and Economics.","Money has flowed into Chinese stocks in part because the central bank is cutting interest rates to support growth, something the U.S. Federal Reserve did in 1998 to revive confidence amid Russia\\u2019s sovereign debt default and the collapse of the hedge fund Long-Term Capital Management.","Like the dot-com bubble, China\\u2019s hi-tech boom is creating a new class of wealth -- at least on paper. No less than 12 technology billionaires have been minted this year, according to the Bloomberg Billionaires Index. They include Beijing Tianli Mobile\\u2019s Chairman Qian Yongyao and He Ye, a co-founder of Shenzhen InfoTech Technologies Co. That stock has surged 274 percent since the start of January and is valued at 2,628 times earnings.","\\u201cMany of these technology companies have bubble-type valuations as speculators take advantage of popular concepts to ramp up shares,\\u201d said Haitong\\u2019s Chen, a strategist in Shanghai. \\u201cOnly a very small group, say 5 percent or 10 percent, will make it to become larger companies.\\u201d"]', 'http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-04-07/u-s-dot-com-bubble-was-nothing-compared-to-today-s-china-prices', '', 'n', '2015-04-08 06:00:24'),
