(360, 1, 'Asia’s Richest Woman Looks Past China to Dodge Iron Gloom ', '["http:\\/\\/media.gotraffic.net\\/images\\/inkv4Y.ZNLig\\/v3\\/488x-1.jpg"]', '[" Asia-Pacific\\u2019s richest woman is gearing up to start shipments from her $10 billion iron ore project in Australia. Even with prices at 10-year lows, she\\u2019s displaying no lack of confidence in the mine\\u2019s success.","Billionaire Gina Rinehart\\u2019s ace? Her mine isn\\u2019t relying solely on sales to China, the biggest iron ore buyer. This limits the project\\u2019s exposure to a market where steel demand is judged to be peaking.","Instead, she\\u2019s locked in supply contracts with three of the largest iron ore consuming Asian nations outside of China.","\\u201cThey feel very confident. Roy Hill has a massive advantage in that it has diversified its markets,\\u201d Philip Kirchlechner, Perth-based director of Iron Ore Research Pty. said by phone. \\u201cThey have buyers from three of the other major iron ore importing markets.\\u201d","Roy Hill, Australia\\u2019s largest single iron ore mine, is on track to commence exports from September, adding 55 million tons a year of output to a market already saturated by a growing surplus. It\\u2019s even accelerating the mine\\u2019s schedule, seeking to hit its planned capacity at the fastest pace of any project built in Western Australia\\u2019s iron-rich Pilbara region.","Her partners, South Korea\\u2019s Posco, Japan\\u2019s Marubeni Corp. and Taiwan\\u2019s China Steel Corp. have committed to take half of the mine\\u2019s annual output, Barry Fitzgerald, chief executive officer of Roy Hill Holdings Pty, said in an e-mailed response to questions. \\u201cWe also have significant commitments from steel mills across Asia for a large portion of the remaining sales volume,\\u201d he said.","Posco, which has a 12.5 percent stake, expects to begin importing about 7 million metric tons annually from Roy Hill in September, Kang Min Suk, a spokesman at Posco, said by phone on Wednesday. South Korea\\u2019s biggest steelmaker rose 2.8 percent to 253,500 won in Seoul trading at 11:21 a.m local time, trimming its decline this year to 8 percent.","The mine\\u2019s products \\u201care in demand by steel mills, no matter what the pricing environment,\\u201d Fitzgerald said.","Rinehart, with an estimated wealth of about $12.1 billion according to the Bloomberg Billionaires Index, sold a 30 percent stake in Roy Hill to the three partners.","\\u201cIn an environment like now where it\\u2019s quite risky and there are buyers defaulting, it\\u2019s good to have reliable offtakers,\\u201d said Kirchlechner, formerly head of marketing at Fortescue Metals Group Ltd. and an ex-Rio Tinto Group executive in China.","Rinehart\\u2019s judgment on iron ore follows her acute call on thermal coal, agreeing to sell most of her assets in 2011 for $1.26 billion. The fuel fell in 2012 to its worst annual price slump in seven years.","Iron ore prices had the largest quarterly loss since 2009 in the three months through March and plunged to a decade low of $47.08 a dry metric ton last week, before climbing back to $48.06 on Tuesday, according to Metal Bulletin Ltd. data. Last week\\u2019s level was the lowest since 2004-2005 based on the data and on annual benchmarks compiled by Clarkson Plc, the world\\u2019s largest shipbroker. The plunge prompted junior miner Atlas Iron Ltd. to suspend its shares from trading on Tuesday while it reviews its operations and considers asset sales.","A forecast global surplus means those developing new mine projects face sharp revisions to revenue estimates, said Andrew Hodge, a Sydney-based analyst at Wood Mackenzie Ltd. \\u201cUndoubtedly you are going to have lower revenues and lower margins than they anticipated,\\u201d Hodge said by phone.","Building Roy Hill after large competitors completed a $120 billion program of expansions may mean the mine has benefited from cheaper labor and contract rates. Staffing costs on some projects are about 20 percent lower amid weaker competition for labor, Hodge said.","The exit of higher cost production will probably see the iron ore market return to balance by 2023, according to Wood Mackenzie. Prices may rise from next year, the China Iron &amp; Steel Association forecasts.","\\u201cThrough history, the best returns are generally built during the downtown,\\u201d said Carl Adams, Perth-based national sector leader for mining at KPMG. \\u201cYou could argue that Gina Rinehart has built in the downturn and that she\\u2019s poised for the upside.\\u201d"]', 'http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-04-07/asia-s-richest-woman-looks-past-china-to-dodge-iron-gloom', '', 'n', '2015-04-08 06:15:49'),
